<div class="content-wrapper">
<div class="main-content max-width min-width center">
<div class="layout-cell layout-cell-12">
<div class="layout-cell-pad-main">
<img class="foto" src="http://servicosweb.cnpq.br/wspessoa/servletrecuperafoto?tipo=1&amp;id=K4791433P3"><div class="infpessoa">
<h2 class="nome">Ricardo Bins di Napoli</h2>
<ul class="informacoes-autor">
<li>
<span class="img_link icone-informacao-autor"></span>Endere&ccedil;o para acessar este CV: http://lattes.cnpq.br/0018710144049443</li>
<li>
<span class="img_cert icone-informacao-autor"></span>&Uacute;ltima atualiza&ccedil;&atilde;o do curr&iacute;culo em 06/05/2014</li>
</ul>
</div><br class="clear" /><div class="title-wrapper">
<h1 class="ui-hidden"></h1>
<hr class="separator">
<p class="resumo">Ricardo Bins di Napoli is Associated Professor 3 at the Department of Philosophy at the Federal University of Santa Maria.  He is Advisor at the Post-graduation Program at the same University. His areas of expertise are concentrated on Ethics and Applied Ethics. 

Had been  Academic Visitor at University of Oxford, United Kingdom in 2012, where  had developed a  investigation on emotions and moral dilemmas. The PhD in Philosophy had been started at Ludwig-Maximilliams University of  Munich (Germany) and concluded  at Pontifical Catholic University of  Rio Grande do Sul (1999). The subject of the thesis was Ethics and Hermeneutics on the ethics of the german Philosopher  W. Dilthey, while  his Master Degreein Philosophy was concluded the Federal University of Rio Grande do Sul on  Ethics and political Violence (1988).  
 
Now he develops a  research on moral dilemmas and moral  responsibility. Has published on the political and moral contractarianism of John Rawls and David Gauthier. Has  published the book "Ethics and the understanding of the other" on the ethics of W. Dilthey (EDPUCRS, 2000). Has edited with other collegues two other books: 1) Ethics and Justice (Ética e Justiça, (Palotti/CNPq, 2003), on  J. Rawls's conception of Justice and 2) Norberto Bobbio: Right, Ethics e Polítics (2005) about the thought of the italian philosopher Norberto Bobbio  . Ricardo has written newspaper's articles about social, political and philosophical issues.

He coordinates the  Workgroup  Ethics of the Brazilian Nacional Association of Pos-Graduation on Philosophy (ANPOF). Chief of the Research Group on Ethics and Applied Ethics from the Brazilian Council of Research (CNPq). He is a member of other two research groups both from the CNPq: 1) Justice and political culture,  2) Knowledge, Language and Morality. 
Had been a member of the Bioethics Committee of the University Hospital of Santa Maria (2008-2011) and  had coordinated the Committee on Research Ethics of the Federal University of Santa Maria (2003-2007).   Has been actively participating in the activities of  the Group of Ethics and Philosophy of Mind of the Federal University of Rio de Janeiro (UFRJ), coordinated by Prof. Dr. Wilson Mendonça.  

Has received financial support from the Brazilian Agency CNPq for the project of research on " Moral Dilemmas" (2008-2010) and has received scholarships from two important Brazilian Agencies (CAPES and the CNPq) and from Germany from the Deutsche Akademishe Austauschdienst  (DAAD).<span style="font-weight: bold" class="texto"> (Texto informado pelo autor)</span>
</p>
